1
00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:05.260
At a basic level, a computer program is
a recipe of instructions that tells your

2
00:00:05.260 --> 00:00:06.400
computer what to do.

3
00:00:06.780 --> 00:00:10.730
When you write a program, you create a
step by step recipe of what needs to be

4
00:00:10.730 --> 00:00:15.390
done to complete a task and when your
computer executes the program it reads

5
00:00:15.390 --> 00:00:18.010
what you wrote and follows your
instructions to the letter.

6
00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:19.420
How nice is that?

7
00:00:20.430 --> 00:00:23.720
The recipe is written in a code called
programming language.

8
00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:27.830
Programming languages are actually
similar to humans spoken languages since

9
00:00:27.830 --> 00:00:30.020
they have a syntax and semantics.

