Now if it's been awhile since your last
grammar class, here's a quick refresher

11
00:00:34.840 --> 00:00:36.220
on syntax and semantics.

12
00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:41.260
In a human language, syntax is the
rules for how a sentence is constructed

13
00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:44.720
while semantics refers to the actual
meaning of the statements.

14
00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:49.860
In English, sentences generally have
both a subject, that's a person, place,

15
00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:54.050
or thing and a predicate, usually a
verb and a statement that explains what

16
00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:59.410
the subject is doing. Let's take the
sentence, Paula loves to program in

17
00:00:59.410 --> 00:01:00.820
Python as an example.

18
00:01:01.430 --> 00:01:06.190
In this sentence, Paula is the subject
and loves to program in Python is the

19
00:01:06.190 --> 00:01:10.900
predicate. To form a sentence that
others can understand, you need to know

20
00:01:10.900 --> 00:01:14.960
both the syntax that constructs the
sentence and the semantics that gives it

21
00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:18.030
meaning. The same applies to
programming languages.

22
00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:22.880
In a programming language like Python,
the syntax is the rules for how each

23
00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:26.550
instruction is written and the
semantics is the effects the

24
00:01:26.550 --> 00:01:31.110
instructions have. Much like spoken
languages, there are lots of programming

25
00:01:31.110 --> 00:01:32.200
languages to choose from.

26
00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:37.660
Each has its own history, features, and
applications but they all share the same

27
00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:38.780
fundamental ideas.

28
00:01:38.780 --> 00:01:42.390
So once you understand the basic
concepts in one programming language, it

29
00:01:42.390 --> 00:01:44.260
becomes much easier to learn another.

30
00:01:44.770 --> 00:01:47.800
Lastly, computers always do exactly
what they're told.

31
00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:51.970
So when you write a program, it's
important to be super clear about what

32
00:01:52.020 --> 00:01:53.360
you want the computer to do.

33
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:57.420
Learning the syntax and semantics of
the programming language you choose will

34
00:01:57.420 --> 00:01:59.210
allow you to do just that.

